snippet.title: Johnny Depp & Amber Heard Controversy Coming To An End
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp & Amber Heard Controversy Coming To An End
✅ Subscribe to us → https://www.youtube.com/c/FilmRoyalty?sub_confirmation=1
🔔 Turn on notifications to never miss a new upload!
✅  Follow us on Instagram → https://www.instagram.com/filmroyalty

About:
Four years later the couple were back in court, but this time in London. However, this was not Amber Heard's case - she had not chosen to be here. This was a libel action Depp had brought against a British newspaper, The Sun. At the heart of the case was his assertion that the allegations of physical abuse were an "elaborate hoax". Depp employed one of the best-known libel barristers in the country to try to prove the claims were untrue.
Over the next three weeks, Heard arrived at court each day and walked past her former husband's fans, who were convinced that it was their hero who was the victim and it was she who had assaulted him. In court her story, photos, memories and the accounts of her friends were all exposed to the world and said by Depp's team and supporters to be part of a plot to falsely prove that he was, as The Sun had claimed in April 2018, a "wife beater".

It was not just the fans and media who were watching carefully. Lawyers were already wondering, if he won, what impact this would have on women coming forward with claims of domestic violence. Outside, Johnny Depp would arrive each day to cheers. But his behaviour and lifestyle were also under the microscope - and a judge has now ruled that The Sun's allegations were "substantially true".

snippet.title: La Doble Vida De Amber Heard Completamente Revelada
snippet.description:
Amber Heard tiene una impresionante carrera en el cine, pero es probable que también conozcas por su vida personal, que muchas veces fue el centro de atención de los medios. Estas son algunas cosas que tal vez no sabías sobre la vida de Amber Heard.

Heard y su ahora ex-esposo Johnny Depp se conocieron en el 2012 en el set de Diario de un Seductor y se casaron en el 2015. En mayo del 2016, Heard solicitó el divorcio y lo acusó de abuso doméstico. Heard escribió en la declaración,

"Durante toda nuestra relación, Johnny fue verbal y físicamente abusivo conmigo. Soporté un excesivo abuso emocional, verbal y físico de Johnny, que ha incluido ataques furiosos, hostiles, humillantes y amenazantes hacia mí cada vez que yo cuestionaba su autoridad o no estaba de acuerdo con él."

Heard también presentó una foto en donde aparece con la cara lastimada. Afirmó que la herida fue causada por un golpe de Depp con su teléfono. Ella le dijo al tribunal,

"Vivo con el temor de que Johnny vuelva a [nuestra casa] sin avisar para aterrorizarme, física y emocionalmente."

Pero la policía no encontró pruebas de ninguna agresión cuando respondió a una llamada por pelea doméstica en la casa de la pareja en mayo del 2016, y Heard se negó a presentar una denuncia penal. El abogado de Depp le dijo a la corte,

"[Heard] está intentando asegurar una resolución financiera prematura alegando abuso. Johnny no puede protegerse a sí mismo ni a Amber del escrutinio de los medios."

Mientras que Heard acusó a Depp de violencia doméstica, ella fue arrestada por presunta violencia doméstica contra su ex pareja, la fotógrafa Tasya van Ree, en septiembre del 2009. Según TMZ, Heard y van Ree discutieron en un aeropuerto, y Heard presuntamente golpeó a van Ree. Fue arrestada y fichada por un delito menor de violencia doméstica, pero el fiscal se negó a seguir adelante con el caso, porque ambas mujeres vivían en California.

Años después, van Ree dijo públicamente que el incidente fue "sobresensacionalizado," y describió a los oficiales que hicieron el arresto como "homofóbicos" - pero en realidad la oficial es una mujer gay, y escribió en Facebook,

"¡No soy homofóbica en lo absoluto! [...] El arresto se hizo porque hubo una agresión (yo lo presencié) y las partes involucradas estaban en una relación doméstica."

Van Ree también emitió una declaración cuando los informes del arresto resurgieron en el 2016, diciendo,

"Es desgarrador que la integridad y la historia de Amber sean cuestionadas una vez más. Amber es una mujer brillante, honesta y hermosa y tengo el mayor respeto por ella. Compartimos 5 maravillosos años juntas y mantenemos contacto hasta el día de hoy."

#AmberHeard

snippet.title: Amber Heard NEVER Actually Loved Johnny Depp!
snippet.description:
💙 Amber Heard NEVER Actually Loved Johnny Depp!  
The love story of Johnny Depp and Amber Heard began with a newbie who is “fascinated” by a Hollywood king. Still, it ended in acrimony with conflicting accounts of what happened played out in a bitter court battle for all the world to see.
Ms. Heard, who is 23 years younger than Mr. Depp, said that when they were together, “it was like we were the only people in the world.”
Ms. Heard said their romantic relationship began in 2011 when they promoted The Rum Diary and recalled how later that year, Mr. Depp invited her to spend a weekend at the Trump SoHo in New York. “We loved the same music, and poetry, and art – we would just sit and talk for hours.”
She described Mr. Depp as “engaging and intellectual and dark and funny,” adding: “I was captivated. I had never been with someone like him.”
But she said Mr. Depp only allowed her to tell a few family members and close friends about their relationship.

A Celeb reacts to Johnny Depp Winning Against Amber Heard

INTRO: If you’re a big fan of pirates, then you must have watched the world-famous series, “The Pirates of the Caribbean.” With world-renowned actor Johnny Depp, the movie has hit charts. Well, we’ve seen a lot of his humor in the movies but is he as happy in real life as he portrays to the world? What truly happened in his relationship with Amber Hear. Well, that’s what we’ll find out today.

Johnny Christopher Depp II is an American actor, musician, and producer. Yes, you read it right, This award-winning actor, has won over 25 awards and 55 nominations. And in Johnny’s 58 years of existence, well, of course, he would have already met someone, married them, and had kids with them. His first spouse was Lori Allison, from 1983-1985, even before he became an actor. Soon, there was Sherilyn Fenn, Winona Ryder, Kate Moss, Vanessa Paradis (with which he had 2 kids), and lastly, his ex-wife, Amber Heard, whom he divorced in 2017, and the main topic of today’s tea. 

But why was Amber and Johnny’s divorce quite a mess? Well, it was a complete and total sham actually, and we all know that, considering the divorce was highly publicized. It’s better to start from the beginning of the story, isn’t it? Johnny and Amber met back in 2011 on the set of “The Rum Diary” and started living together in 2012. In early 2013, Johnny allegedly have been physically violent to his partner when Amber claimed that Johnny has slapped her three times already after she joked about a tattoo that Johnny got on his arm during his relationship with Winona Ryder, and Johnny obviously denied the allegations. In early 2015, specifically on February 3, 2015, the couple married each other in a private and intimate ceremony in their home in Los Angeles. Here’s where fans got a little suspicious with Amber’s story, if Depp has already been abusive, why push with the wedding?

 In around March 3-5 of the same year, the couple went on a three-day trip to Australia, presumable to wind down and enjoy the married life. But according to the actress, it wasn’t as magical as we thought. Amber describes the three-day trip to Australia as a “3-day hostage situation,” in which Johnny was accused by his wife of physically and verbally abusing her while drinking heavily and taking drugs. Johnny, once again, denies the allegations, saying that Amber had lost her temper while they were both talking about a post-nuptial agreement, with very different stories, it’s not wonder the court was confused. On April 21, a few months after the “3-day hostage situation,” the couple arrived in Australia, smuggling their Yorkshire Terrier pets, Boo and Pistol, which they did not declare to customs officials in Queensland. Amber was charged for bringing her dogs into the country illegally and was soon dropped after the couple made an apology video. And suddenly on May 22 of the following year, 2016, the couple separates which was considered to be unsurprising news, but when the reason of the divorce came out, the media and fans wanted to know all about it.

On April 21, a few months after the “3-day hostage situation,” the couple arrived in Australia, smuggling their Yorkshire Terrier pets, Boo and Pistol, which they did not declare to customs officials in Queensland. Amber was charged for bringing her dogs into the country illegally and was soon dropped after the couple made an apology video. And suddenly on May 22 of the following year, 2016, the couple separates which was considered to be unsurprising news, but when the reason of the divorce came out, the media and fans wanted to know all about it.
